caption: Great ambience and very personal service. The menu was fresh and enchanting. Will absolutely recommend this spot to friends. Reasonable prices and large portions. Keep up the great work.

Placed an order on their website, waited an hour, nothing. Call them up, say oh sorry we're very busy today, we haven't been taking orders online, yet my credit card was charged. Then they tell me 30 mins, we'll get it for you. Get a call back immediately, driver says I'm too far (1 mile). Would've been waiting here all day if I hadn't called. Bad customer service, I suggest you order from elsewhere.
Fast, quick and always the best!!

It was AMAZING. Definitely my favorite place so far for sushi! Tasted great and fresh. Sushi was well put together and didn’t fall apart. Dumplings were nice and crispy (how we prefer) and the spring rolls were amazing and so was the sauce that comes with it.!

Well according to uber eats this is the location tho im not sure the name is the same as in the app lol. However i have been ordering from them on uber eats for so long now and i have only been ordering from them. The food is always fresh and service is very quick and they make sure food arrives warm all the time. Also their food is extremely delicious and the portions you get are unbelievable for the price you pay. I love them and their food and they have found themselves a loyal customer! The past two months ive been ordering only from them to my work.
The people working here are very nice, and the food is good.
Great selection for a small restaurant. Been going here for a long time and am never disappointed.
I love this place. I order from them all the time. Great chef and wonderful service. I love their rolls. Everything is always fresh and delicious.

Just ordered pickup from here today. When I went in to pick up the food, I was shocked to see the chef making my food without a mask on. Then, while I was waiting for my food, two customers came in without a mask, and the restaurant employees said nothing. Another customer came in afterwards with a mask, and then decided to wait in the rain (seen in the attached picture) because of the two un-masked customers in the restaurant. I won't be returning to this restaurant, since it seems like they don't care about their customers' health.

Just went recently after it reopened. Fish was fresh, so fresh in fact one of rolls' fish still had scales on it. Ginger however was not fresh... i will still keep my review at 3 star because its just eh

This restaurant is my number one restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to that place. This restaurant used to be great. It was my go-to place. Recently it's under new ownership/management. The food quality is terrible now. We got food poisoning. In addition to getting poisoned, we also got robbed because they were missing about $20 worth of food from our large order. This is the absolute last time we'll ever order from Jin Sushi, aka Wow Sushi and Thai (as this is the name they are using at the moment) again.
Their Chicken coconut soup is a real delicious. Very kind, very friendly. Fish - always fresh, sushi - real professional handmade.
One day food is good and  on another day ,food is terrible. There is no consistency. Good luck, I hope you get there on the good food day.

Haven’t noticed this place since the bus stop is always crowded but thank god i did, been picking up sushi from here ever since, absolutely nothing to complain about & the staff is always extremely nice & helpful.
Tidy small gem hidden by a small train station. Respectful kind staff, the food is very home-y. Overall it was very much enjoyed. Thanks guys for the experience.
Ordered delivery, very spicy pad thai. I got bland tasting food. The reviews had my expectations high and they were not met. Hopefully their dine is much better to math their reviews.
Awesome place. I got bagel rolls, crazy dragon rolls and godzilla rolls. They are soooo big. And they gave us a present, for 2 big sushi  you get 1 small (6 pieces) rolls.

If I could give 3.5 or 3.75 stars I would. I get take out from Jin often. Thai options are done well, though I wish the summer rolls were in a thicker wrapper. The sushi rolls are OK; the Japanese menu I'm less a fan of. The space is a bit tight to dine in, especially when there are loud teenage patrons there.

I’ve never been in person but I order from here for work quite often. They’re very kind on the phone and their delivery person is patient. I’ve been ordering from here for almost two years and they’re very efficient time wise as well. If the order will take over 45 minutes they will let you know they’re busy and to expect a wait time before you place your order. Highly recommended.
Great place great food friendly workers
This is my new favorite sushi restaurant. Besides tasty food for great price, they it’s also located within walking distance from my home.
Great sushi, great prices  and great service. We ordered for delivery and it came super fast. The susi was to die for. A tip is to order extra, you'll want more of it.
Food is amazing but the place have about 4 or 5 tables to sit on so there might be a wait on busy hours. The prices are also great and you get healthy food. The hot tea taste good and it is also free

I have ordered food from this location for pickup along eaten in store last week with my mom. The family who works here is very nice and personable. They constantly come by often to check in and refill your beverages.  My mom ordered the chicken and broccoli with white rice ($7.50). I ordered the chicken teriyaki bento box ($7.50) with a Thai ice tea ($3.50). I also ordered a taro bubble tea to go ($3.50). Each lunch order comes with a choice of soup or salad. I ordered the miso soup, which I thought tasted about average. My mom got the salad and thought it tasted average.  The chicken and broccoli were delicious. However, to some, it might be on the saltier side and has an excess amount of sauce. Personally, I love foods that are salty and has a lot of sauce. The chicken teriyaki bento box came with two shrimp shumai pieces with a very generous amount of chicken and vegetables. The chicken teriyaki was on par with other places in terms of taste and texture.
Fresh and Very Good

Awesome, fresh food in a super cute and cozy setting. Will definitely visit again~  Right off the Kings Highway B/Q stop. Tucked away from the hustle and bustle of the highway proper as it's on Quentin and east 16th.

Me and 4 of my friends bought meals and when we asked for water we were completely ignored. We asked again very politely and she screamed at us that they don't serve water there. I don't know what we did. We were so polite and respectful. Nobody was there so we weren't holding them up. We all bought a decent amount of food. She also added $2 on my bill without telling me I only found out when she charged my credit $2 more. Because I get notifications on my phone. I was told it was for tip. But a simple sign letting you know beforehand that you'll be charged for tip would have been nice. We ordered our food she handed it to us we sat down ate and left. We were getting the evil eye the entire time.

What a lovely small place! Simple but very stylish, and the staff is super kind as well. A complimentary green tea was also served us during our lunch which was great and is a really thoughtful gesture. The lunch special is also available on the weekend, so I had a vegetable+tofu pad thai served w/ a little salad and 2 spring rolls, only for $7.5. My husband had a salmon fried rice which was also quite a big portion, and everything tasted really good! Can't wait to get back for more delicious meals.

Ordering online was quick and easy, the prices were good. I really enjoy pad tai  and theirs was no good. The fried was very good and spicy. I never got that taste of tai basil that I enjoy or lemon grass from the pad tai. Appetizers were very good,  but weren't traditional tai cuisine, we had scallion pancake and fried gyozo , chicken satay.  The satay flavor was good,. We also ordered teriyaki chicken,  which was good but not tai. More Japanese flavors at this restaurant,  .

Food was great!! The outdoor presentation doesn't seem promising but what a great surprise with the food! My husband shared a Caterpillar Sushi roll, and I ordered Thai pad noodles with brown day sauce and seafood and he got Spicy Thai rice with shrimp. Our bellies were very happy!

A gem in the midst of Kings Highway! My friends introduced me to this place this past summer and I highly recommend it. I can testify I've ordered sushi and bento boxes for lunch to go especially when I have extra time before the next train arrives. It's so convenient since it is located under the train station. They also have a $5 Thai Iced Tea in a large container (that thing where they put soup when you order for Chinese food) which will surely satisfy any Thai iced tea lovers :D Affordable and REALLY YUMMY sushi and the staff are always so nice. I also have to say that they have a good choice of music there!

I'm a regular here. The staff has gotten to know me well and are always super nice with everyone. Fun fact: the restaurant is family owned.  Other than that, I suggest everyone try the Ginza Roll. Very tasty. Prices are cheap and food quality is great. Definitely recommend for some quick food.
